article.headline: UCF 99, Jacksonville 62
article.story: ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) -- Josh Peppers scored 24 points to lead Central Florida past Jacksonville 99-62 Monday. Central Florida (5-0) hit its first six shots of the second half and outscored Jacksonville 25-4 in the first 6:32 of the half to take a 35-point lead. The Knights led by as many as 43 points as every Central Florida player scored. Central Florida hit 65.4 percent from the floor and outrebounded Jacksonville 33-16. Tony Davis finished with 14 points and seven rebounds for Central Florida. Jermaine Taylor added 12 points and Stanley Billings had 10. Ben Smith led the Dolphins (3-3) with 14 points. Marcus Allen had 13 points and Evan Jefferson and Lehmon Colbert finished with 11 points each. Central Florida hit 11 of its first 12 shots from the floor, including 6 of 7 from three-point range, to build a 30-17 lead during the first 10 minutes. The Knights cooled off during the next 10 minutes, but still managed to shoot 68 percent from the floor in the first half and led 50-36 at intermission.
